Class OBAnnotationInclusion

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.build.OBAnnotationInclusion

  • public class OBAnnotationInclusion
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a specification of a set of annotations to be copied from any relevant OWL entities to the corresponding frames-based entities that have been generated.

    • Method Detail

      • setValueSeparators

        public void setValueSeparators(java.lang.String valueSeparators)
        Defines one or more characters that are to act as value-list separators. When value-separators are specified, all annotation-value strings derived from the OWL entities will be split accordingly in order to provide multiple annotation-values for the corresponding frames-based entities.
        Parameters:
        valueSeparators - String containing set of individual characters, each of which can act as a list-value separator

      • addValueSubstitution

                                 java.lang.String framesValue)
        Defines a potential value for the OWL annotations that if found will be replaced by another specified value when the annotation on the frames-based entity is created.
        Parameters:
        owlValue - Annotation-value derived from OWL entity
        framesValue - Annotation-value to be substituted for frames-based entity
